<collectingCountry box="[370,442,1628,1652]" name="Brazil" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Brazil</collectingCountry>
: Northeast, Central-West, Southeast and South regions (MA, CE, RN, BA, AL, DF, MG, ES, SP, RJ, SC) (
<bibRefCitation author="Ribeiro" box="[341,495,1663,1687]" firstAuthor="Ribeiro" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref42583" refString="Ribeiro, J. R. I. (2007) A review of the species of Belostoma Latreille, 1807 (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Belostomatidae) from the four southeastern Brazilian states. Zootaxa, 1477, 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="2007">Ribeiro 2007</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,1483,1796]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Comments: Some of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[487,608,1701,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anurum">
<emphasis box="[487,608,1701,1724]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">B. anurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens studied so far do not differ from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Palisot de Beauvois, 1805)" baseAuthorityName="Palisot de Beauvois" baseAuthorityYear="1805" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subspinosum">
<emphasis box="[1127,1305,1700,1724]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">B. subspinosum</emphasis>
(Palisot de Beauvois, 1805)
</taxonomicName>
subspecies in features of the phallus, and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[823,943,1737,1760]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anurum">
<emphasis box="[823,943,1737,1760]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">B. anurum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might eventually prove to be a junior-synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Palisot de Beauvois" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[252,428,1772,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Belostomatidae" genus="Belostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subspinosum">
<emphasis box="[252,428,1772,1796]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">B. subspinosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
